 Ngqamakhwe - Ngqamakhwe police arrested a 41-year-old man for alleged murder of his elder brother aged 46. "It is alleged the two brothers had a misunderstanding on Tuesday, at about 23h00, at their ancestral home, which is at Frystat Locality, Vananda Village, Ngqamakhwe," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "It is further alleged that the 46-year-old man was armed with an axe, but he was stabbed by the suspect on his upper body. "It was only noticed on Wednesday, at about 05h00, that the 46-year-old man had passed away. "The 41-year old suspect is expected to appear before the Ngqamakhwe Magistrate’s Court on Thursday on a murder charge." Capt Manatha said that the identity of the deceased will be withheld until all family members are officially informed of his death. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 